body:
@kai-zhong your snapshot is still generating, and you did have a few unclean shutdown. 

Can you run this? `geth snapshot traverse-state --datadir ... --datadir.ancient ...` It should detect the corrupted state.

And regarding the error `block body missing, can't freeze block 8285195` it's pretty weird. According your logs, it says `Loaded last fast-sync pivot marker       number=15,080,103`, your node just finished snap sync. This block should be inserted into freezer directly, instead of migrating from key-value store. I am curious how did you sync up your node?

> 
@rjl493456442  thanks so much.
it's sovled. just restart my computer(windows), and sync normally again.
